{{Infobox company | name = Arbitration Place | logo=Arbitration Place Toronto Logo June13 2012.png | logo_size=216px | location = [[Toronto]] | industry = [[Law]] | products = [[Arbitration]] | key_people = Kimberley Stewart, CEO and Founder | homepage = http://arbitrationplace.com }}
'''Arbitration Place''' is an internationally affiliated [[arbitration]] facility and legal centre located in the [[Bay-Adelaide Centre]], in [[Toronto]], [[Canada]].
==Profile== Arbitration Place hosts domestic and international arbitrations and facilitates these arbitrations through legal and administrative services such as on-site court reporting, videoconferencing, technical support, closed-captioning, interpreters, translators, and in-house legal counsel.<ref name="globalarbitrationreview">Karadelis, Kyriaki. "This must be the Place." Global Arbitration Review, 19 April 2012.[http://www.globalarbitrationreview.com/news/article/30483/this-place/] Retrieved May 1, 2012.</ref> Resident arbitrators include [[Yves Fortier (lawyer)|Yves Fortier]], past President of the [[London Court of International Arbitration]], and the Honourable [[Ian Binnie]], former Justice of the [[Supreme Court of Canada]].<ref name="nationalpost">Melnitzer, Julius. "Ex-Supreme Court Justice Ian Binnie joins Lenczners." National Post. April 11, 2012. [https://archive.is/20120411230958/http://www.nationalpost.com/Supreme+Court+Justice+Binnie+joins+Lenczners/6439117/story.html] Retrieved May 1, 2012.</ref><ref>Zillman, Claire. "Former Canadian Supreme Court Justice Joins Toronto Litigation Boutique." The Am Law Daily. April 16, 2012. [http://amlawdaily.typepad.com/amlawdaily/2012/04/former-canadian-supreme-court-justice-joins-toronto-litigation-boutique.html] Retrieved May 1, 2012.</ref><ref>Morrisson, Meredith. "Binnie eager to see 'other side of the adjudication ladder'." Law Times. April 16, 2012. Page 5.</ref> As Ian Binnie notes in an interview with [[Evan Solomon]], the aim of Arbitration Place is to position Canada as a forum for international commercial arbitration.<ref>Evan Solomon, Host (April 2012). "House Additions-Ian Binnie." The House: Web Exclusives. CBC. [http://www.cbc.ca/thehouse/promonoblog/2012/04/13/house-additions---ian-binnie/] Retrieved June 13, 2012. Binnie's remarks on Arbitration Place appear between 19:20 and 19:55.</ref>
== Partnerships == Arbitration Place maintains partnerships with the [[London Court of International Arbitration]] (LCIA) and with ICC Canada, the Canadian national committee of the [[International Court of Arbitration]] of the [[International Chamber of Commerce]].<ref name="nationalpost" />
